Hello! Welcome to the home page of the University of South Carolina, Columbia. I can help you with some basic questions regarding application, location, student housing, dining on campus, etc. How can I help you?
Hey boy, how do you find a place to live?

The campus housing is primarily for first-year students. Most of the university's students and visitors use off-campus accommodation. Many people find www.zillow.com useful in finding an apartment or room. Did you get the answer?
Hi boy how much is the application fee?
The undergraduate application fee is $65 (common application fee without waiver); for general graduate program is $50. Other applications may cost more.
Hi boy, how to apply? Hey boy, how's student accommodation going

Housing prices on campus range from $3100 to $6600 per year. term. For more details, please see the webpage: https://sc.edu/about/offices_and_divisions/housing/index.php; The cost of off-campus apartments in Columbia ranges from $500-$1500. A room can be found for 350-600 USD. Columbia offers a variety of traditional, family-friendly housing options and apartments. You can expand your search to sites like ApartmentFinder.com, ApartmentList.com, Zillow.com, Trulia.com and Homes.com. Did you get the answer?

There are a number of lunch spots on and around campus. Please see the lunch locations here https://sc.edu/experience/grab_a_bite/campus_restaurants_list.php
